President Muhammadu Buhari, on Wednesday, held a meeting with aspirants seeking to contest the position of chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC). The discussion held behind closed doors. Present at the meeting were Mai Mala Buni, Yobe governor and chairman of the APC caretaker committee; Boss Mustapha, secretary to the government of the federation (SGF); and Ibrahim Gambari, chief of staff to the president. Aspirants present at the meeting were Abdullahi Adamu, Abubakar Yari, Saliu Mustapha, George Akume, Tanko al-Makura, Sani Musa and Mohammed Saidu Estu. Also, Ali Modu Sheriff, former governor of Borno, who has withdrawn from the APC chairmanship race, was also present at the meeting. The APC convention is scheduled for March 26. Photo: Sunday Aghaeze Photo: Sunday Aghaeze Photo: Sunday Aghaeze Photo: Sunday Aghaeze 